After quite a tense primary election, it has been the baroness, Susana Díaz, who has won the PSOE's primary election. Not much seems to have changed in the party, and the voices calling it unreformable may have been proven right, once again.

- @post_event: We'll have to see how she fares...

@sanchez_elected
title: Pedro Sánchez wins the primary
subtitle: [? if not (up_congreso_s <= psoe_congreso_s and podemos_congreso_s <= psoe_congreso_s): Given the dire state of the party, we'd have to support his candidacy for him to win. [-1 resources] ?]
